<p>The way this works is each div for all posts, coding posts and personal posts have markdown in them that generates an unordered list with links to posts. In markdown each post has a category declared in it’s front matter. I use a for loop to generate each. By default in the CSS above you can see all post is shown and the separated personal and coding posts are set to display none. Next is the JS to tell the selector which div to display and which divs to hide, switching each time a new selection is made:</p>

<figure class="highlight"><pre><code class="language-html" data-lang="html"><table class="rouge-table"><tbody><tr><td class="gutter gl"><pre class="lineno">1
